NOTE:PROFESSIONAL PROFILE\n\nCareer History: Previously at The Carlyle Group as part of the Sub-Saharan Africa investment team. Co-founded Alterra Capital Partners in 2020 alongside Genevieve Sangudi\, Eric Kump\, and Idris Mohammed when the team exited Carlyle.\n\nNotable Deals: Involved in Alterra's acquisition of a stake in Cobra Group Holdings (mining and fire safety equipment) and the consortium investment in Chill Beverages.\n\nAreas of Expertise: Africa-focused private equity; deal sourcing and execution; portfolio value creation; consumer goods and industrials sectors.\n\nSources:\nhttps://www.bloomberg.com/profile/person/23657705\nhttps://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/latest-news-headlines/carlyle-s-sub-saharan-africa-team-exiting-to-launch-alterra-capital-58808707\nhttps://www.africaprivateequitynews.com/p/south-africa-alterra-led-consortium
